The '''China Girls Mathematical Olympiad''' ('''CGMO''') is a [[list of math competitions|math competition]] with a [[Mathematical proof|proof]]-based format similar to the [[International Mathematical Olympiad]]. It was originally organized in 2002 for teams of girls representing different regions within [[China]]. Later, the Chinese organizers decided to invite other nations to send teams of girls from their countries. [[Russia]] has participated at least since 2004. The [[United States]] participated in 2007-2012.
== Further reading == *[http://www.maa.org/pubs/nov07web.pdf "At the China Girls Math Olympiad" in ''FOCUS,'' November 2007 pages 10–11]
