{{Orphan|date=February 2017}}

The '''Ghana School Feeding Programme''' (GSFP) is a pilot project to provide food to children at school.<ref name=gbc>[http://gbcghana.com/news/30249detail.html School Feeding to be extended to JHS]</ref> It is run by the GSFP Secretariat in partnership with international agencies including the [[World Bank]], the [[World Food Programme]], the [[Partnership for Child Development]] and [[UNICEF]], as well as national organizations including [[Canadian International Development Agency]] (CIDA), the US Agency for International Development ([[USAID]]) and the Dutch embassy.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Lynch|first1=Amy|title=INACTION OR IN ACTION’, THE EFFECTIVENESS OF THE  GHANA SCHOOL FEEDING PROGRAMME: THE CASE OF  NTRANOA SCHOOL, CAPE COAST, GHANA|publisher=University of Limerick|url=http://www.ul.ie/ppa/content/files/Amy_Lynch.pdf|accessdate=18 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Bob|first1=Ato|title=School Feeding in Africa: Ghana’s success|url=http://www.mediablackberry.com/index.php?oid=12164|website=African Bulletin|publisher=Media Blackberry|accessdate=18 September 2014}}</ref>

