{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} {{Infobox University |image = ISIT logo.jpg |image_size = 100px |name = Instituto Superior de Intérpretes y Traductores |motto = Comunicación entre culturas (Communication Among Cultures) |established = 1964 |type = [[Private school|Private]] | |president = Ximena Iglesias Carrillo (principal) |endowment = |undergrad = Translation, Interpretation, and Languages |postgrad = Terminology, Diplomatic Studies, and Translation and Interpretation on Comparative Law |faculty = 200 |city = [[Mexico City]] |state = |country = {{flagcountry|Mexico}} |campus = Urban |mascot = |website = [http://www.isit.edu.mx/ isit.edu.mx] }}
The '''Instituto Superior de Intérpretes y Traductores, S.C.''' (in [[English language|English]]: Superior Institute of Interpreters and Translators), commonly known as '''ISIT''', is a private [[university]] located in [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]. It focuses on [[Language interpretation|interpretation]] and [[translation]], and it became the first institution in the [[Americas]] to academically acknowledge these disciplines as [[bachelor degree]]s.
ISIT has worked along with [[Fondo de Cultura Económica]] (Economic Culture Fund), the [[Instituto Nacional de Bellas Artes]] (National Institute of Fine Arts), [[Asociación de Escritores de México]] (Writers Association of Mexico) and the [[National Autonomous University of Mexico]] (UNAM). It is also a member of the [[American Translators Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atanet.org/certification/eligibility_approved.php#mex|title=American Translators Association|accessdate=January 12, 2009}}</ref>
It relies on [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]], [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] and [[Italian language|Italian]] for fields such as [[automotive]], [[Chemistry]], [[Engineering]] and [[Politics]].
ISIT's library stores 2500 volumes, 250 videocassettes, 90 audio cassettes and 20 maps, and it is recognised by UNAM's Centro Universitario de Investigaciones Bibliotecológicas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cuib.unam.mx/mapabiblio/datosbiblio.pl?biblio=708 |title=Centro Universitario de Investigaciones Bibliotecológicas: ISIT |accessdate=January 12, 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080226003933/http://cuib.unam.mx/mapabiblio/datosbiblio.pl?biblio=708 |archivedate=February 26, 2008 }}</ref>
