{{Infobox convention | image = | status = | genre = [[Bisexuality]] | venue = | location = Varies | country = Varies | first = October 1991 | last = | founder_name = [[Fritz Klein (sex researcher)|Fritz Klein]] et al. | organizer = | filing = | attendance = 200&ndash;1000 (approx.) | website = }} The '''International Conference on Bisexuality '''('''ICB'''), also known as the '''International BiCon''', was a periodic gathering of [[bisexual]] [[activists]] and [[academics]] from around the world.
Started by [[Fritz Klein (sex researcher)|Fritz Klein]] and a group of fellow activists, the first ICB was held in [[Amsterdam]] in 1991 and followed the concept of a [[BiCon (UK)|BiCon]] started in the UK in 1984. The last one was 2010 in London.[http://www.bisexualindex.org.uk/index.php/links]
