{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Use South African English|date=August 2015}} The '''Minister of Education''' used to be a [[Minister (government)|Minister]] in the [[Cabinet of South Africa]], with the responsibility of overseeing the [[Department of Education (South Africa)|Department of Education]], including South Africa's schools and universities.
On 10 May 2009 newly elected president [[Jacob Zuma]] split the education portfolio into that of the [[Minister of Basic Education (South Africa)|Minister of Basic Education]] and that of the [[Minister of Higher Education and Training (South Africa)|Minister of Higher Education and Training]].
