{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Education, Ghana Burh |nativename = |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = GES (Ghana Education Service) logo.jpg |logo_width = 290px |logo_caption = |seal = MOE (Ministry of Education) logo.png |seal_width = 270px |seal_caption = |formed = 1957 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Ghana|Republic of Ghana]] |headquarters = {{Flag|Ghana}} |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[ Hon. Matthew Opoku Prempeh ]] |minister2_pfo = |chief1_name = Mr. Enoch Cobbinah |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |parent_agency = Ghana Education Service |child1_agency = [[National Accreditation Board (Ghana)]] |child2_agency = |child3_agency = |child4_agency = |website = {{Official website|http://www.moe.gov.gh/moe/}} |footnotes = }} {{Politics of Ghana}}
The '''Ministry of Education (MOE)''' is a multiportfolio [[government ministry]] of [[Ghana]], responsible for the government and management of Ghana's education. It is responsible for the [[curriculum|national education curriculum]], primarily instituted by Ghana Education Services, which is part of the Ministry.<ref>[http://www.moess.gov.gh/ges.htm Ministry, Ghana Education Services] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090119111917/http://moess.gov.gh/ges.htm |date=2009-01-19 }}</ref>
The Ministry of Education was established under the Civil Service Law 327 and under the [[PNDC]] Law 1993 with the mandate to provide relevant education to all Ghanaians.<ref>http://www.moe.gov.gh/site/about/</ref>
The Ministry's [[main offices]] are located in [[Accra]].
== History ==
The first Minister of Education in [[Ghana]] was J.B. Erzuah under the [[Nkrumah government]] in 1957.
== Agencies ==
* [[National Accreditation Board (Ghana)|National Accreditation Board (NAB)]] * [[West African Examinations Council|West Africa Examination Council (WAEC)]] * Council For Technical And Vocational Training (COTVET) * The National Board For Professional And Technician Examinations (NABPTEX) * National Council For Tertiary Education (NCTE) * Ghana Library Authority (GLA) * Ghana Academy of Art and Science * Funds And Procurement Management Unit * Ghana National Commission For UNESCO
