{{Infobox Government agency|name=Ministry of Education of Russia|nativename_a={{lang|ru|Министерство просвещения Российской Федерации}}|seal=MES emblem.png|seal_caption=|picture=|picture_caption=|formed=|preceding1=|minister1_name=|minister1_pfo=|dissolved=|superseding=|jurisdiction=[[Government of Russia]]|headquarters=[[Tverskaya Street|Tverskaya]] 11, [[Moscow]], [[Russia]]|coordinates={{coord|55|45|38.50|N|37|36|35.21|E|type:landmark_region:RU|display=inline,title}}|budget=|employees=|child1_agency=|child2_agency=|website={{URL||https://edu.gov.ru/}}}}

'''Ministry of Education of the Russian Federation''', also called '''Ministry of Enlightenment of the Russian Federation''' ({{lang-ru|Министерство просвещения Российской Федерации}}) was established on 17 May 2018 after the split of the [[Ministry of Education and Science (Russia)|Ministry of Education and Science]] into two parts. It oversees school education and [[school accreditation]] in the [[Russian Federation]]. 
The minister is [[Olga Vasilieva (politician)|Olga Vasilieva]]; earlier she was a head of the parent ministry. The agency has its headquarters in [[Tverskoy District]], [[Central Administrative Okrug]], [[Moscow]].<ref>"[http://eng.mon.gov.ru/obr/cont/ CONTACT] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111115062101/http://eng.mon.gov.ru/obr/cont/ |date=2011-11-15 }}." Ministry of Education and Science. Retrieved on 1 November 2011. "''Address'': Tverskaya street, 11, Moscow, 125993" - [http://mon.gov.ru/obr/kont/ Address in Russian] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111105050338/http://mon.gov.ru/obr/kont/ |date=2011-11-05 }}: "ул.Тверская, д.11, г.Москва, ГСП-3, 125993"</ref> (The second child agency is the [[Ministry of Science and Higher Education (Russia)|Ministry of Science and Higher Education]].) 

